definition: abbr. for 青海[Qing1 hai3], Qinghai Province

sentences.english: Then you truly are a fool, Prince Frog.
sentences.chinese: 那你就着實是個傻瓜，青蛙王子。

sentences.english: "There were thousands of them, " a villager told a local newspaper.
sentences.chinese: “青蛙的數量成千上萬，”某村民向當地報社提到。

sentences.english: A frog and a squirrel were neighbors.
sentences.chinese: 一隻青蛙和一隻松鼠是鄰居。

sentences.english: Once, a group of frogs lived in a little pond.
sentences.chinese: 從前，有一羣青蛙居住在一個小池塘。

sentences.english: Béka was a frog-faced boy a head taller than the others.
sentences.chinese: 貝卡是個長着青蛙臉的男孩，比其他人高出一個頭。

sentences.english: The frog asks, ‘How do I know you won’t sting me?’
sentences.chinese: 青蛙問，‘我怎麼知道你會不會蜇我？’

sentences.english: Day micro-light, frogs to find me.
sentences.chinese: 天微亮，青蛙就找到了我。

sentences.english: The leg action of the breaststroke may have originated by imitating the swimming action of frogs.
sentences.chinese: 蛙泳中腿部蹬水的動作很可能是模仿青蛙的泳姿而來。

sentences.english: One of them had a little boy and a frog.
sentences.chinese: 其中一個有一隻青蛙和一個小正太。

sentences.english: The princess refused to keep her promise to the frog.
sentences.chinese: 公主拿到玩具後拒不履行之前給青蛙的承諾。

sentences.english: The largest frog in the world is the giant salamander in China.
sentences.chinese: 最大的青蛙的世界，是在中國大鯢。
青蛙的朋友冬木來跨越。

sentences.english: Liven up a girlie night in with this fabulous Frog Prince Lighted Wine Stopper.
sentences.chinese: 奇異的青蛙王子低度葡萄酒瓶塞讓美女之夜煥發生機。

sentences.english: The porcelain clay that you will use for your craft frogs will dry in a nice shade of white.
sentences.chinese: 瓷土，你會使用你的手藝青蛙幹漂亮的白色陰影。

sentences.english: " I curiously ask, "chicken is the frog.
sentences.chinese: 我好奇地問，“田雞是青蛙。”

sentences.english: A tadpole metamorphoses into a frog.
